      "title": "Syllables",
      "subtitle": "Is-Sillabi — splitting words into syllables",
      "intro": "In Maltese, splitting a word into syllables makes spelling easier — you can hear (and write) every sound. Three rules: each syllable has only one vowel; the second syllable starts with a consonant; if two consonants meet in the middle, split between them.",
      "facts": [
        "Each syllable has only one vowel.",
        "The second syllable starts with a consonant.",
        "If two consonants meet in the middle, split between them.",
        "Examples: omm → omm; mara → ma-ra; kelma → kel-ma."
      ],
